      <h1>About Amoura</h1>
      <p>Our values, our practices, our vision</p>
    </header>

    <nav>
      <a href="index.html">Home</a>
      <a href="about.html">About</a>
    </nav>

    <section>
      <h2>What Amoura Is</h2>
      <p>Amoura is a sacred and intentional community rooted in love, touch, presence, and truth. It is not a retreat, nor a business, nor a movement — it is a lived space where human beings honour connection with themselves, each other, and the earth.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Body, Touch, and Trust</h2>
      <p>We believe the body is sacred. Touch, when given and received with awareness, is a pathway to healing and connection. In our space, physical closeness is welcomed, not hidden — and we cultivate trust through consent, clarity, and slow invitation.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Intimacy and Consent</h2>
      <p>Consent is not just permission — it is presence. At Amoura, we honour boundaries as sacred and changeable. We practice open communication, body awareness, and trust-building, creating a safe ground for honest intimacy to emerge without pressure or shame.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Spiritual Practice</h2>
      <p>Our rituals are simple, elemental, and embodied. We honour the sun, the earth, the water, the breath. We move, sing, cook, sit in circle, bathe, and rest — not as performance, but as devotion to life itself.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Living Together</h2>
      <p>Amoura is not a place you visit for a weekend — it is a rhythm. We cook together, clean together, garden together, build spaces for stillness and celebration. Our community values transparency, co-creation, and interdependence.</p>
    </section>

